2.10	Shiradi	Shiradi	Shiradi or Shirady (Kannada: ಶಿರಾಡಿ)is a village on NH 48 which runs from Mangaluru to Bengaluru.The shiridi ghat starts from small temple "garadi chamundashwari temple"near Gundya at the border of Dakshina kannada &amp; Hassan districts. The village is situated in Puttur taluk of Dakshina Kannada district. The ghat section of Western ghats through which NH-48 passes is called Shiradi Ghat.	
